  <h2 class="subheader">About us</h2>
<p>Cities are made of people, after all. Knowing your city is only possible through knowing yourself. So when we connect personal and urban data, people will be able to see their impact on the city and how the city affects them and their personal and group outcomes. </p>



<p>This data-enabled relationship between individuals, groups, and the city is a new type of civic intelligence. </p>



<p>We are helping create this new source of civic intelligence by providing the tools for people to safely contribute personal data and mash it up with urban data and the personal data of others.</p>



<p>This will unlock new urban and civic knowledge that will encourage people to ask and answer questions together about their cities.</p>




