<p>Using voluntary personal data contributions, it also brings untold granularity of civic insights. </p>

 

<p>The technology is already available, whether its cameras, personal data stores, twitter, the web, and smartphones and their sensors.</p>



<p>On top of these we can throw analysis and visualization to form the basis of data driven discussions. </p>



<p>We expect these new data-driven discussion to accelerate the way groups form around their common urban interests and common personal data sources. </p>



<p>Our hope, of course, is that this new empowerment leads to advanced civic insights and actions.</p>



